items.title: Market posts biggest weekly gains in 6 months; rupee hits record low
items.description: During the week, the Indian rupee touched fresh record low of 84.73 and ended 20 paise lower at 84.69 per dollar on December 6 against the November 29 closing of 84.49.

items.title: These smallcaps give double digit return as outperformance continues
items.description: On the sectoral front, Nifty Realty and PSU Bank indices added 5 percent each, Nifty Metal and Media added 4 percent each, while Nifty IT index was up nearly 4 percent.

items.title: Wall Street adds to stock, rate cut bets after 'Thanksgiving buffet' jobs data
items.description: The S&P 500 and the Nasdaq rose on Friday, up 0.25% and 0.8% respectively, further bolstered by upbeat forecasts from Lululemon Athletica, Ulta Beauty and other companies.
